author: rice@dccc.org
title: House Speaker Says GOP Has "Obligation" to "Eliminate" Medicaid. Young Kim MIA.
text:
Kim & House GOP would risk health coverage for 82,000 people in CA-40
With inflation rising and the price of eggs hitting all time highs, Young Kim and House Republicans are scheming to rip away health coverage for millions of American families to fund tax breaks for billionaires and wealthy corporations.
House Speaker Mike Johnson doubled down on the GOP bait and switch, telling Punchbowl News that he intends to cut Medicaid: “We have a stewardship obligation to root that out and eliminate it.”
Last week, far-right Republicans scored a huge victory when the Budget Committee adopted an amendment that ensured Republicans would seek at least $1.5 trillion in cuts to vital programs like Medicaid.
Despite campaigning on making life more affordable for Californians, Kim is poised to do just the opposite.
DCCC Spokesperson Courtney Rice:
“Young Kim knows exactly what she is doing. After Republicans accepted millions of dollars from billionaires like Elon Musk, they are choosing to screw over hardworking families with cruel cuts to Medicaid in order to fund tax breaks for their same billionaire backers.”

author: Adam Eckert
title: SEALSQ Corp Shares Are Moving Higher After Hours: What's Going On? - SEALSQ (NASDAQ:LAES)
text:
SEALSQ Corp LAES shares closed Thursday up more than 60%, and the stock isn’t slowing down after hours. Shares are up more than 3% in extended trading after the company announced it regained compliance with Nasdaq listing rules .
What Happened: After the market close on Thursday, SEALSQ said it received formal written notice from the Nasdaq confirming that the company regained compliance with the Nasdaq’s minimum bid price requirement.
SEALSQ received a letter from the Nasdaq on Aug. 1, stating that the company was not in compliance with the $1 minimum bid price requirement for continued listing on the Nasdaq. The company was required to maintain a minimum bid price of at least $1 for 10 consecutive trading days prior to Jan. 28.
SEALSQ said it was informed that it regained compliance after its shares traded above the $1 level from Dec. 11 to Dec. 24. Shares are responding favorably to the announcement that the matter is now closed. SEALSQ shares are now up more than 2,000% over the past month, per Benzinga Pro .
SEALSQ stock rallied more than 60% during normal trading hours on Thursday after the company announced the launch of SEALQUANTUM.com Lab, designed to support organizations transitioning to quantum-safe encryption.
“As quantum technologies become a reality, the need for quantum-safe encryption solutions grows increasingly urgent,” said Carlos Moreira , CEO of SEALSQ.
“Our SEALQUANTUM.com Lab is more than just a platform, it’s a commitment to future-proofing our clients’ security. By combining cutting-edge research with actionable tools, we’re empowering businesses to navigate the complexities of quantum cryptography with confidence.”
SEALSQ describes itself as “a company that focuses on developing and selling semiconductors, PKI and post-quantum technology hardware and software products.”
Check This Out: SEALSQ Launches SEALQUANTUM.com Lab To Help Businesses Transition To Quantum-Safe Encryption
LAES Price Action: SEALSQ shares were up 0.23% in after hours, trading at $8.78 at the time of publication Thursday, per Benzinga Pro .

text:

Jay Biggerstaff-USA TODAY Sports Gambling content 21+. The New York Post may receive an affiliate commission if you sign up through our links. Read our editorial standards for more information.
Patrick Mahomes’ receiving corps is as good as it’s been in years.
Over the offseason, Chiefs brass went out and signed wide receiver Marquise “Hollywood” Brown and drafted speedster Xavier Worthy with the No. 28 overall pick.
Although Brown will miss the opener with a shoulder injury, Worthy’s presence alone will help Mahomes in the passing game in Thursday’s season opener against the Ravens.
Mahomes had perhaps the worst season of his career in 2023 in the passing department with a career-high 14 interceptions, a career-worst 7.0 yards per attempt and a 92.6 passer rating.
Vegas oddsmakers are expecting some improvement with his new weapons this season, though, pegging Mahomes as the favorite to lead the NFL in passing yards.

author: Redacción LA FM
title: Ideam alerta por lluvias para fin de año | La FM
text: [Geraldine Rozo Amórtegui ](/autores/geraldine-rozo-amortegui) Ideam lanza preocupante advertencia sobre lluvias y tormentas en fin de año Se anticipa que el país experimentará nubosidad y lluvias, con posibles tormentas eléctricas en las regiones del Pacífico y la Amazonía. En un reciente pronóstico del tiempo, Daniel Useche, jefe encargado de la oficina de alertas y pronósticos del Ideam, proporcionó detalles sobre las condiciones climáticas esperadas para el fin de semana en Colombia. Se anticipa que el país experimentará nubosidad y lluvias, con posibles tormentas eléctricas en las regiones del Pacífico y la Amazonía, así como en áreas específicas de Antioquia, Norte de Santander, Santander, Boyacá, Cundinamarca, Caldas, Risaralda, Quindío, Tolima y Huila. Lea también: [Ideam anticipa tardes frías y lluviosas en Bogotá](https://www.lafm.com.co/bogota/ideam-anticipa-tardes-frias-y-lluviosas-en-bogota) No obstante, se espera que la región Caribe y la Orinoquía mantengan condiciones secas. Para Bogotá, se pronostica un cielo entre parcial y mayormente nublado, con posibilidad de precipitaciones hacia el oriente y suroriente de la ciudad en las primeras horas de la mañana, y lluvias en zonas del norte y noroccidente durante la tarde. En otras áreas, se espera un clima mayormente seco, con cielos parcialmente nublados y temperaturas alrededor de los ocho y 21°C. Por su parte, Useche indicó que, "este fin de semana tendrá condiciones de nubosidad, se comprobaría de lluvias, acompañadas en algunos casos de tormentas eléctricas, principalmente en sectores de la región del Pacífico y amazónica, y también en áreas de los departamentos de Antioquia, el sur de Norte de Santander, algunas áreas del este y sur de Santander, también en sectores de Boyacá, Cundinamarca hacia la Sabana Centro". Le puede interesar: [Ideam hace dura advertencia sobre el sol en diciembre: hay que cuidarse más](https://www.lafm.com.co/bogota/ideam-hace-dura-advertencia-sobre-el-sol-en-diciembre-hay-que-cuidarse-mas) Deslizamientos En cuanto a las alertas por deslizamientos, se reporta un total de 379 municipios en algún nivel de alerta, siendo 76 de ellos considerados en alerta roja. Destacan los departamentos de Nariño, Cauca y Meta, con el mayor número de municipios en alerta. La región andina presenta 200 municipios en algún nivel de alerta y 139 en alerta naranja por riesgo de deslizamientos. Es importante destacar que este pronóstico y las alertas están sujetos a cambios, por lo que se recomienda estar atentos a las actualizaciones de los informes meteorológicos.
